Add interactivity, Canvas rename, teal rebrand + metallic gunmetal

Deepen the Demi prototype from a static UI into an interactive app driven
by a Zustand store, rename Artifacts -> Canvas, drop in the Demerzel logo,
and introduce brand teal #008B8B with a metallic gunmetal dark theme.

Functionality:
- Chat: composer sends real messages; token-streamed assistant replies with
  model provenance + thinking; build-style prompts generate a live Canvas;
  new-chat creation; auto-titling; auto-scroll
- Model Manager: Pull animates real progress -> Installed; Load/Unload/Delete
  mutate state and reflect in the model switcher
- Cowork: Run now adds a running->success run; Active and Keep-awake toggles
  persist; detail panel reflects live store state
- Customize: Light/Dark/System retheme live; Local-only mode hides cloud
  models; MCP Allow/Ask/Deny persists; provider keys + Ollama URL bound
- Model switcher respects local-only mode and offers Pull

Rebrand / design system:
- New teal ramp (base #008B8B) + --brand-teal token + teal->turq->cyan
  gradient (bg-brand-gradient-teal) on Canvas headers
- Dark theme retuned to a cooler metallic gunmetal palette with a subtle
  brushed-metal sheen (.metal-surface / .metal-rail) on rail + top bar
- Uploaded Demerzel logo used in the rail brand area and favicon

Rename: Artifacts -> Canvas across types, store, views, nav, components
(CanvasView, CanvasPanel, CanvasDoc, canvasId, canvasCount). Shared Toggle
primitive added to ui.tsx. Built with 4 additional subagents.
